During the practice, the student:
Collaborates with the non-university partner to develop a practice plan and formulate practice objectives.
Implements the tasks outlined in the plan.
Submits a written practice report, which critically analyzes and evaluates the acquired experience and the perspectives on folklore processes revealed within the project (including the methods used, their application, results obtained, etc.).
Presents the research findings to the non-university partner (where fieldwork was conducted) in a suitable format and manner.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide an opportunity for the application of folklore-related knowledge in various non-university settings (such as another research institution, organization, company, NGO, etc.) and to analyze this experience.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, the student will be able to: Apply specialized knowledge to carry out a practical project at a non-university partner. Critically analyze the knowledge and experiences acquired during the practice and assess the possibilities of applying folklore-related knowledge, including the use of various sources, the significance of context, limitations of use and impact, and creative interpretations.
